        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 11 at 6:16PM MDT until July 11 at 6:45PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
near Pawnee Buttes to over Briggsdale, or along a line from 41 miles
north of Fort Morgan to 27 miles northeast of Greeley, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Trained spotters reported. At 558 pm, a trained spotter
reported 2 inch diameter hail 5 miles south southeast of
Grover.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Keota, Pawnee Buttes, Briggsdale and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. These storms have produced dangerous
hail and are capable of producing damaging winds.

These dangerous storms are capable of producing large hail driven by
severe winds! Seek shelter now inside a sturdy structure and stay
away from windows! If you are caught outdoors, cover your head and
neck.</instruction>
